## TL;DR: What Every Cushion Cut Band Buyer Must Know First

The cushion cut diamond band is the most geometrically misunderstood purchase in the engagement ring follow-on market. Most buyers assume any diamond band works alongside any engagement ring. With a cushion center stone, that assumption creates an ugly visible gap at the point where the band meets the engagement ring setting — a problem so common it has a name.

**Contrarian Truth — The Band Gap:** A standard straight-profile diamond band placed next to a cushion cut engagement ring will not sit flush. The cushion's four-cornered, slightly squared setting creates a wider profile at the base than a round brilliant does, and a straight band curves away from that profile at the connection point. The result is a visible gap on each side of the engagement ring that looks like a design mistake rather than a pairing choice. Most jewellers will not tell you this before you buy.

