## What Is a Cushion Cut Diamond Band?

A cushion cut diamond band is a diamond-set ring featuring cushion-cut stones, designed to be worn alongside a cushion cut diamond engagement ring as a wedding band, anniversary band, or stacking band. Unlike round brilliant bands where the stones can be any shape because the ring profile is circular, a cushion cut diamond band is engineered specifically for the cushion's four-cornered geometry — matching the stone shape creates visual cohesion that no round-brilliant band fully achieves.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The cushion cut diamond band market is one of the fastest-growing segments in diamond jewellery in {{year}}. As cushion cut engagement rings have climbed to third in market share, the demand for matched cushion bands has followed — and Blue Nile's expanded cushion band inventory (seven-stone, full eternity, bezel eternity, across natural and lab in all metals) now offers genuine breadth that did not exist as recently as three years ago.

What separates a well-chosen cushion band from a poor one is not the price or the total carat weight. It is understanding The Band Gap — the geometric incompatibility between straight-profile bands and cushion ring settings — and choosing a band configuration that either eliminates the gap entirely or embraces it as a design element.

