## Seven Stone Cushion Diamond Band

The seven stone cushion band is the most practical cushion cut wedding band for everyday wear. It features seven cushion-cut diamonds set in a prong or channel configuration across the top half of the ring — a half-eternity layout that leaves the palm side of the ring smooth and metal-only.

**Why seven stone works best with cushion.** The stones occupy only the top portion of the shank, which means they end well before the junction point where the engagement ring sits. The Band Gap still technically exists, but because the stones don't extend into that zone, there is no stone-to-stone interruption. The metal shank meets the engagement ring setting smoothly, and the band's cushion stones echo the center stone's shape along the visible top arc.

[![Cushion cut diamond band yellow gold seven stone lifestyle](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/LifeStyleV4/FineJewelry/604710/604710_Y_2_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings?stoneShape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**Sizing advantage.** Unlike full eternity bands, seven stone bands can be resized — there are no diamonds on the shank sides that prevent adjustment. This matters significantly for buyers whose finger size changes seasonally, post-pregnancy, or over decades.

**Natural vs lab for seven stone cushion bands.** The case for lab is stronger in the wedding band market than anywhere else in the diamond stack. The individual stones in a seven stone band are small — the 1ct total weight option distributes roughly 0.14ct per stone. At that size, the visual difference between a natural H-I/SI1-SI2 stone and a lab F-G/VS2-SI1 stone is negligible. The price difference is not. A [1ct natural seven stone in 14K White Gold is $3,830](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/seven-stone-cushion-diamond-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-201942?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational); the [1ct lab equivalent at higher F-G grade is $2,980](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/seven-stone-cushion-lab-grown-diamond-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-202245?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — $850 less for a better colour grade.

