## Full Eternity Cushion Diamond Band

A full eternity cushion cut diamond band wraps cushion-shaped stones all the way around the shank — no metal-only section, diamonds visible from every angle. It is the most visually dramatic band option and the strongest choice for buyers who plan to wear the band as a standalone ring or as a high-impact stacking piece.

[![Cushion cut diamond full eternity band yellow gold lifestyle on hand](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/LifeStyleV4/DiamondBasics/604403/604403_CSH_0225CT_Y_2_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings?stoneShape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**The sizing problem with full eternity bands.** Full eternity bands cannot be resized after purchase because the diamonds wrap the entire circumference — cutting the shank to adjust size destroys stones. Before ordering a full eternity cushion band, confirm your exact ring size with a jeweller's mandrel. Do not estimate. An incorrectly sized full eternity band requires replacing the entire ring rather than a simple resize.

**The Band Gap and full eternity.** Full eternity bands are better than seven-stone bands at minimising The Band Gap visually — the continuous diamond wrap creates a complete diamond border that draws the eye away from the metal junction point. However, the gap still physically exists unless the band has a curved profile. If The Band Gap is a primary concern, pair a full eternity band with a cushion engagement ring that has a lower, wider profile rather than a high-set solitaire.

**Lab vs natural at full eternity.** At total carat weights of 2ct–8ct, the price difference between natural and lab full eternity cushion bands is dramatic. A [natural 2ct full eternity in 14K White Gold is $6,420](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/cushion-cut-eternity-ring-in-14k-white-gold-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-256751?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational); the [lab 2ct equivalent with better colour grade is $4,460](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-eternity-ring-in-14k-white-gold-2-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-256752?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — $1,960 less for a higher colour grade. At 6ct, the gap becomes extreme: natural is $24,310 versus lab at $7,000 — $17,310 difference for the same visual appearance.

