## Bezel Cushion Diamond Eternity Band

The bezel cushion eternity band sets each cushion stone in a full metal collar (bezel) rather than prongs. The bezel wraps the stone completely, creating a low, smooth profile with no prongs to catch on clothing or lift over time.

[![Cushion cut diamond bezel eternity band rose gold lifestyle shot](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/LifeStyleV4/DiamondBasics/606575/606575_CSH_0150CT_R_1_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings?stoneShape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**Why bezel works uniquely well with cushion.** The cushion's soft, rounded corners are visually echoed by the bezel collar's curved metal walls. Bezel settings for cushion stones look more cohesive than bezel settings for square stones (where the metal walls create hard corners) or for rounds (where the bezel circle fights the stone's brilliant geometry). For cushion specifically, bezel creates an almost Art Deco — seamless, sophisticated, modern.

**Bezel and The Band Gap.** The bezel setting's continuous metal wall provides a smoother transition at the ring junction than prong settings. The bezel collar itself acts as a partial bridging element between the band and the engagement ring setting. Not a complete solution to The Band Gap, but meaningfully better than prong-set bands in this regard.

**Durability advantage.** The bezel's full metal enclosure protects each cushion stone from edge impacts — relevant for daily-wear bands where stones on the outer perimeter of the ring routinely contact hard surfaces. For buyers with active lifestyles, a bezel cushion band is the most durable option available.

